      • authors

        protected static final String[] authors

        Parameters:
        injector - the injector provided by the Selene implementation

      • getInstance

        public static <T> T getInstance(Class<T> type,
                                Class<?> extension,
                                InjectorProperty<?>... additionalProperties)
        Gets an instance of a provided Class type. If the type is annotated with Extension it is ran through the ExtensionManager instance to obtain the instance. If it is not annotated as such, it is ran through the instance Injector to obtain the instance based on implementation, or manually, provided mappings.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type parameter for the instance to return
        Parameters:
        type - The type of the instance
        extension - The type of the extension if extension specific bindings are to be used
        additionalProperties - The properties to be passed into the type either during or after construction
        Returns:
        The instance, if present. Otherwise returns null

      • bindUtility

        public static <T> void bindUtility(Class<T> contract,
                                   Class<? extends T> implementation)
        Creates a custom binding for a given contract and implementation using a custom AbstractModule. Requires the implementation to extend the contract type.

        The binding is created by Guice, and can be annotated using Guice supported annotations (e.g. Singleton)

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type parameter of the contract
        Parameters:
        contract - The class type of the contract
        implementation - The class type of the implementation

      • debugRegisteredInstances

        protected void debugRegisteredInstances(ServerEvent.ServerStartedEvent event)
        Prints information about registered instances. This includes injection bindings, extensions, and event handlers. This method is typically only used when starting the server.
        Parameters:
        event - The server event indicating the server started

      • except

        public void except(@Nullable
                   @Nullable String msg,
                   @Nullable
                   Throwable... e)
        Handles a given exception and message using the injected ExceptionHelper instance. Uses the global preferences as defined in GlobalConfig to use either the ExceptionLevels.FRIENDLY or ExceptionLevels.MINIMAL level. Additionally this also performs the preference for whether or not to print stacktraces, using GlobalConfig.getStacktracesAllowed()
        Parameters:
        msg - The message, usually provided by the developer causing the exception. Can be null.
        e - Zero or more exceptions (varargs)
